Rating: 3
Why 3 forks instead of 4? Why on earth would you take the time to fry this when you can broil it in no time, get a nice caramelization on the tomatoes, and (if you cover your baking sheet with foil) totally clean up in seconds? Just line a baking sheet with foil, crinkling it up a bit to allow the olive oil to run underneath, grease the foil with olive oil to keep the fish from sticking, salt and pepper both sides of the fish and top with remaining ingredients. Broil about 4 - 6 inches from broiler (depending on whether you have gas or electric broiler) for about 15 minutes and you are done. EASY.

