Rating: 4
Great flavor, but I needed something lower in fat, with less prep and clean-up, so I created a baked version that turned out fantastic. In a covered baking dish, mix together only 1 Tbsp olive oil, and all the ingredients except the fish. (I added a couple of sundried tomatoes that I'd soaked and chopped.) Place the fish on top, pat it to get a little oil on it, flip the fish over and press it down into the tomatoes and olives. Cover and bake at 375 degrees for about 10 minutes; turn the fish and bake another 5 minutes or so. Voila! No messy stovetop, less oil, FABULOUS flavor!

