Rating: 4
I've made this almost every week for the past five. Here's how I like it: Salt and pepper the fish and then dip in flour. Saute then remove. I generally chop the parsley, but I use pitted olives from the jar (from Trader Joes), and put in 5 cubes of frozen garlic and 1-2 cubes of frozen basil (also from Trader Joe's). If I'm really busy, I use the frozen parsely cubes as well. I put whole (not halved) grape tomatoes. I saute all of these ingredients together to save time. When it is ready (less than 5 minutes), I deglaze with white wine for a few minutes and then return the fish to warm on top of the mixture. I sometimes add zucchini in the mix as well. I use the frozen brown rice packages from TJ's. It's so easy and takes no time at all. Perfect for a weeknight meal. It's wonderful.

