This was really delicious. I tweeked it a bit, based on reviews, and will make it again and again the same way. I dredged the tilapia filets in panko seasoned with s&p and garlic powder, sauteed in 1/4 cup oil, loved the crust. I also sub'd fresh basil for the parsley (all I had), that could go either way as I love both. Finally, I had fresh zucchini on hand, so I sliced and sauteed that with crushed red pepper and olive oil for a couple minutes before adding the sliced grape tomatoes, garlic and kalamata olives (my local grocery market sells them pitted - yay - so they are easy to chop). All in all, a very easy, delicious and healthy one-dish meal! Enjoy!

