Rating: 3
Second time making this recipe. Thought I'd share that I was able to find pitted kalamatas at the deli counter at my local grocer, rather than the canned/jarred food aisle. Made this a lot quicker and easier. Also in response to the recent reviews, using a full 1/4 cup of olive oil with the salt and pepper on the outside of the fish yields a nice crispy crust on the fish which adds a lot of flavor that the tilapia, which is rather bland, needs. Also, the crust seals in the juices. You may be able to cook it with less oil, but you don't get the same effect of the golden outside crust and the fish may dry out before it is completely cooked. Also, I think kalamatas or other type of greek olives are important for the flavor of the dish. Plain old black olives sliced in a can just wouldn't do this justice.

